20596.「また 会いましたね <cs_pchero>さん。\n バトリンピック・予選のチ:
We meet again <cs_pchero>. Here are the
checkpoints for the Battlympics and
Qualifiers.

20597.「お忘れですか？\n 前に 月光の花を集めていただいた者ですよ。\n その節は:
Did you forget? I am the one who collected the
moonlight flowers before. Thank you for your
help on that occasion.

20598.「今は こちらで 予選の係員を務めていますよ。\n <cs_pchero>さんと:
I'm a qualifying attendant here now. I was
wondering if <cs_pchero> and I could meet up
again here.

20599.「あなたなら きっと 決勝バトルを勝ち抜き\n 優勝することも 夢ではないんでし:
I bet you wouldn't dream of winning the final
battle and becoming the winner.

20600.「まあ それも 予選を突破すればの話……:
Well, that is if you make it through the
qualifying rounds.

20601.「残念ながら あなたが 闘士の割符を手に\n 戻ることはないでしょう。:
Unfortunately, you will never get your
Fighters' Tally back.

20602.「……あなたは 余計なことを知ってしまった。\n そんな あなたに 生きていても:
You have learned unnecessary things. There are
people who don't want you to live.

20603.「先ほどは まんまと 逃げられましたが\n やはり ここで待っていれば 現れまし:
He got away with it earlier, but he would have
shown up if I had waited for him here. You are
very disciplined, aren't you?

20604.「今度こそ 逃がしませんよ。\n 我が主のために 死んでもらいます！:
You won't get away this time. You will die for
my Lord!

20605.「どうやら 手助けの必要は なかったようだな。: Apparently, they didn't need any help.

20606.「ああ。こいつ 逃げようとしてたんで\n ちょいとばかし なでといたぜ。:
Ah. He was trying to escape, so I gave him a
little nudge.

20607.「しかし アンタが 参加してるのを狙って\n こいつが 係員をやってたんなら\n:
But if this guy was working as a valet to get
you in, this tournament doesn't look too
legit...

20608.「さて それじゃ オレは失礼する！\n ……この男のことは まかせてもらうぜ。\:
Now then, if you'll excuse me. I'll take care
of this guy. I'll take care of this guy. I'm
the one who caught him.

20609.「アンタも 聞きたいこととかあるだろうが\n オレのほうの用件を 優先させてもら:
I'm sure you have questions you want to ask
me, but my business takes precedence over
yours. And don't forget this one!

31993.クラークに\n闘士の割符を 渡した！: I gave Clark the Fighters' Tally!

31994.「……確かに これは 闘士の割符。\n これで <pc>選手の予選は\n 終了と:
...Indeed, this is Fighters' Tally. This
concludes the qualifying round for
<pc> players.

31995.「そして 同時に 第１回バトリンピックの\n 予選全体も 終了とさせていただきま:
And at the same time, the entire preliminary round of the first Battlympics is also coming to an end. As a matter of fact, you were the
last one.

31997.「おめでとうございます！！\n あなたは バトリンピック決勝バトル\n ４人目の:
Congratulations! You are the fourth
participant in the Battlympics Final Battle to
win!

31998.「ほう。<pc>は 残ったのか。\n まずは おめでとうと言わせてもらおう。:
Hou. So <pc> stayed. First, let me
congratulate you.

31999.「これは セインズ選手。\n もしかして 予選結果を聞きにこられたので？:
This is Sainz. Perhaps he came to ask about
the qualifying results?

32000.「どうしても 落ち着かなくってな……。\n そろそろ 全参加者の予選が終わって\:
I just couldn't help but feel a little restless... I thought that by now all the participants would have qualified and the
results would be in, right?

32001.「ンフフフ……。\n 何を 心配することが ありましょう？\n セインズ選手は:
What is there to worry about? Sainz is the
clear winner.

32002.「わずか ４名だけの 決勝進出者の中に\n 同じ ジェイコフ氏の弟子が ふたりも:
I was surprised to see two of Mr. Jakov's students among the only four finalists. I was surprised to see two of Mr. Jaykoff's
disciples among only four finalists.

32003.「オレは 元弟子だけどな。\n ……っと ウワサをすれば なんとやらだ。:
I'm a former apprentice. I'm a former
apprentice.

32004.「チッ……。\n まーた 余計なヤツがいるぜ。:
Elaina, there's someone who doesn't need to be
here.

32005.「……んで どうだった <pc>？\n 予選は 無事 突破できたのか？:
So...how did it go? Did you make it through
the qualifying rounds?

32006.「ンフフフ……。\n <pc>選手も セインズ選手も\n 見事 予選を突破なさい:
Well done to both <pc> and Sainz for
making it through the qualifying rounds.

32007.「セインズも 参加してんのかよ……。\n まあ とにかく 修行は達成できたわけだ:
Sainz is in on it too... well, at least you've
accomplished your training. Then take this
with you.

32008.「ところで 予選の順位は どうだったんだ？\n セインズと <pc>の\n どっ:
By the way, how did you finish in the
qualifying rounds? Who won, Sainz or
<pc>?

32009.「ンフフフ……。\n セインズ選手が 予選１位通過。\n <pc>選手が 予選４:
Sainz qualified in 1st place. <pc>
qualified in 4th place.

32011.「クッ…… いい気になるなよ セインズ！\n 決勝では 必ず <pc>が テメー:
Don't get cocky, Sainz! In the finals, I'm
gonna make sure that <pc> is gonna
make you smile!

32012.「まあ 予選なんて しょせん お遊び。\n バトルマスターの実力とは 関係ないか:
Well, qualifying is just for fun. It has nothing to do with the battle master's ability. After all, battle masters have to
fight, right?

32013.「もちろん 決勝バトルで 当たっても\n 後輩相手に 負けるつもりなんて\n こ:
Of course, I have no intention of losing to a
junior opponent in the finals!

32014.「……そういうワケだ <pc>。\n 決勝で戦えるのを 楽しみにしてるぜ。\n:
...That's why <pc>. I look forward to
seeing you in the finals. Don't let me down!

32015.「ンフフフ……。じつに すばらしいっ！\n 同じ師を持つ ふたりのバトルマスター:
Very wonderful! Sparks flying between two
battle masters who share the same master! It's
on fire!

32016.「バトリンピック・決勝バトル……\n これは がぜん 盛り上がってまいりましたよ:
The final battle of the Battlympics...it's
getting more and more exciting! Oh, no...
